onyatt, Somerset, England":"Donyatt, Somerset, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Shandos","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of Hungarian   Sandor  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Sandor","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Bela, Laszlo, Andras, Attila, Erzsebet, Geza, Imre, Sandor, Tamas, Tibor, Zsolt.","Hungarian (<b>Sándor</b>): from the personal name <i>Sándor</i>, Hungarian form of   Alexander  .","Jewish (from Hungary; <b>Sándor</b>): adoption of the Hungarian surname in 1 above because it has some sounds in common with the original German-based surname."]}]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":1,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrix Shandos was born about 1336, in Chichester, Sussex, England, her father, Lord Robert de Chandos, was 27 and her mother, Margaret Botreaux, was 21. She married Sir Roger de Chichester in 1351, in Donyatt, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1379, in Devon, England, at the age of 44."},"et":{"Abt 1336–1379":"umbes 1336–1379","1336–1379":"1336–1379","1336–1370":"1336–1370","1352–1388":"1352–1388","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1316–Female":"1316–Surnud","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1379":"1379","1388":"1388","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","Abt 1336":"umbes 1336","1351":"1351","1370":"1370","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, England","Donyatt, Somerset, England":"Donyatt, Somerset, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1336–1379":"noin 1336–1379","1336–1379":"1336–1379","1336–1370":"1336–1370","1352–1388":"1352–1388","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1316–Female":"1316–Kuollut","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1379":"1379","1388":"1388","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","Abt 1336":"noin 1336","1351":"1351","1370":"1370","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, England","Donyatt, Somerset, England":"Donyatt, Somerset, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1336–1379":"environ 1336–1379","1336–1379":"1336–1379","1336–1370":"1336–1370","1352–1388":"1352–1388","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1316–Female":"1316–Décédée","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1379":"1379","1388":"1388","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","Abt 1336":"environ 1336","1351":"1351","1370":"1370","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Angleterre","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, Angleterre","Donyatt, Somerset, England":"Donyatt, Somerset, Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Beatrix Shandos est née environ 1336, à Chichester, Sussex, Angleterre, son père, Lord Robert de Chandos, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Margaret Botreaux, avait 21 ans. Elle a épousé Sir Roger de Chichester en 1351, à Donyatt, Somerset, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1379, à Devon, Angleterre, à l’âge de 44 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1336–1379":"um 1336–1379","1336–1379"